## Getting Started

### 1. Prerequisites

- Python {{ python_version }}
- Terraform >= 1.10.0
- AWS CLI configured with appropriate credentials.

### 2. Infrastructure Deployment

```bash
cd terraform
terraform init
# Copy the example vars and update them
cp terraform.tfvars.example terraform.tfvars
# Update variables.tf or terraform.tfvars with your OIDC settings if using BFF
terraform apply
```

### 3. Agent Development

```bash
cd agent-code
# Create a virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate  # or .venv\Scripts\activate on Windows
# Install dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev]"
# Run tests
pytest
```

